column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Gonuhanu is fidgeting with nervousness.
Speak with the distracted Hanu and slay any beasts that appear.
Speak with the distracted Hanu again.
Report to Gonuhanu.
Oh... Where could he be?
Y-You there! You look fierce enough to brave the untamed wilds. Please, I'm in dire need of help...
A friend of mine journeyed southwest to Cave Kikitola a while ago, and still hasn't returned. I'm beginning to fear the worst has happened...
While it's likely he's simply lost track of time staring at the rainbow moss, I keep thinking about all the beasts skulking about... Please check up on him for me, if only to set my heart at ease.
I'll stay here in case he comes back, but in the meantime, visit the cave and search for him. I wager no other Hanu will be nearby, so he shouldn't be hard to spot.
My friend likely got caught up in the beauty of Cave Kikitola, but I would be grateful if you could check up on him. I will stay here in case he returns.
Ah, these waters get more beautiful every time I come...
Sensing a distracted prey, creatures move in for the kill!
What was that noise? Can't I gaze at the moss in peace...?
Wait, you're...you helped us bring back Ihih'hana! You're a friend of Wuk Lamat, yes? What are you doing in this cave?
Fiends, here? Oh, I didn't even hear them until the commotion was nearly over...
I owe you thanks for your courage! And now that my reverie has been broken, I should return to my friend. He must be worried sick.
He returned! He looked slightly unsettled, but none the worse for wear otherwise.
That cave is where we gather the rainbow moss used in our medicines. It has long been held sacred as a healing spot due to its tranquil scenery.
I haven't been since the great storm, and was worried that perhaps it had suffered damage in the floods... I am glad to hear that nothing has changed.
But more than anything, I'm glad my friend returned safely. Had you not come along, the day may have been much darker!
